UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 569/GA
1 (c) Any special judge[ so] selected under this subsection shall have all the
2 powers and responsibilities of a regular judge of the court.
3 (2) A retired justice or judge serving as a special judge shall be compensated as
4 provided by KRS 21A.110.
5 Section 2. Whereas litigants have a constitutional right to an impartial arbiter
6 and attorneys should not be deterred from zealously representing the best interests of
7 their clients by requesting the disqualification of a judge to ensure this right is protected,
8 and as the citizens of this Commonwealth have an interest in a judiciary whose
9 impartiality in specific cases should be above reproach, an emergency is declared to exist,
10 and this Act takes effect upon its passage and approval by the Governor or upon its
11 otherwise becoming a law.
